## If you're finding it difficult to recruit participants with access needs

{{ insetText({
  "HTML": "<p>It's not acceptable to provide a service which hasn't been tested with users with access needs.</p>"
}) }}

Consider recruiting people with access needs who aren’t your users, but perform a similar role. For example, administrators, managers or financial users.

This is not ideal but is significantly better than doing no research or testing with users who are not representative of the users of the service. 

If you are still struggling, you can use the recruitment agency <a href="https://www.criteria.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopner noreferrer" >Criteria (opens in new tab)</a> to recruit participants.

You'll need to write a screener and a business case for using Criteria. To get help, use the <a href="https://ukgovernmentdfe.slack.com/archives/CMS9V0JQL" rel="noopner noreferrer" target="_blank">user research channel on Slack</a>.


